1 AMEND House Bill No. 2061, Page 6, Section 173.002, Line 50, by inserting after the word
2 "amended" the phrase ", except that those complaints solely containing instances of political or
3 religious speech protected under the First Amendment to the Constitution of the United States or
4 the Constitution of Missouri shall not be reported, compiled, or published by the coordinating
5 board for higher education"; and
6
7 Further amend said bill, page, and section, Lines 51-54, by deleting all of said lines and inserting
8 in lieu thereof the following:
9
10 "(5) The Title VI coordinator shall compile an annual report on complaints, except those
11 complaints that solely contain instances of political or religious speech protected under the First
12 Amendment to the Constitution of the United States or the Constitution of Missouri, of
13 antisemitic discrimination and harassment monitored, reported, and investigated under this
14 section. Such report shall be published on the website of the coordinating board for higher
15 education and submitted to the general assembly before July first of each year.
16 (6) No educational institution shall create a list, registry, or database of students based on
17 their religious or political views, opinions, or expressions, which are protected under the First
18 Amendment to the Constitution of the United States or the Constitution of Missouri."; and
19
20 Further amend said bill by amending the title, enacting clause, and intersectional references
21 accordingly.
